INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (95,1,'2010-05-06 17:13:36','2010-05-06 16:13:36','EPiServer stores language resources in XML file sin the \"lang\" folder of the site.\r\n<blockquote>At startup, your EPiServer site will load all the .xml files in the ~/lang directory, alphabetically. A DOM of all language resources will be built in memory, adding all elements from each .xml file, and then cached for the rest of the application life-time (if you change one of the files, it will automatically trigger a reload.) <em>Source: </em><a href=\"http://labs.episerver.com/en/Blogs/Steve-Celius/Dates/112266/112267/Compare-and-keep-language-files-in-sync/\"><em>http://labs.episerver.com/en/Blogs/Steve-Celius/Dates/112266/112267/Compare-and-keep-language-files-in-sync/</em></a></blockquote>\r\nThis means you can add your own XMLÂ languageÂ resources for things like control labels on your templates. It is best practice to leave the EPiServer langauge files intact and create your own files.\r\n\r\nIf you need to override an existing element you can do so, this works particularly well because all the XML files are loaded into a DOM, and any existing elements are overwritten by the later element (alphabetically).\r\n\r\nTo avoid conflicts with existing language files you could simply create a new XML element to contain your translations, for example:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">&lt;language name=\"English\" id=\"EN\"&gt;\r\n      &lt;mywebsitename&gt;\r\n           &lt;home&gt;Home in English&lt;/home&gt;\r\n      &lt;/mywebsitename&gt;\r\n &lt;/language&gt;</pre>\r\n<strong>Accessing Translations</strong>\r\n\r\nCalling Translate:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">LanguageManager.Instance.Translate(\"/standard/home\")</pre>\r\nFor the XML:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">&lt;language name=\"English\" id=\"EN\"&gt;\r\n      &lt;standard&gt;\r\n           &lt;home&gt;Home in English&lt;/home&gt;\r\n      &lt;/standard&gt;\r\n &lt;/language&gt;</pre>\r\nThis will output the string \"Home in English\" if the current culture is English.\r\n\r\n<strong>References</strong>\r\n<a href=\"http://labs.episerver.com/en/Blogs/Steve-Celius/Dates/112266/112267/Compare-and-keep-language-files-in-sync/\">http://labs.episerver.com/en/Blogs/Steve-Celius/Dates/112266/112267/Compare-and-keep-language-files-in-sync/</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://danielsaidi.wordpress.com/tag/episerver/\">http://danielsaidi.wordpress.com/tag/episerver/</a>','EPiServer Translate and XML','Some notes on the EPiServer language XML files and their correct usage.','publish','open','open','','episerver-translate-and-xml','','','2010-05-15 23:11:41','2010-05-15 22:11:41','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=95',0,'post','',1);
