INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (118,1,'2010-05-31 21:45:14','0000-00-00 00:00:00','I\'m setting up a new project using N2 CMS but don\'t have a clear procedure for downloading and setting up an N2 site. I\'m going to use the MVC templates example site as a starting point so make sure you have ASP.NET MVC 2 installed.\n<h3>Downloading the Source</h3>\nEither get the latest release from CodePlex atÂ Â <a href=\"http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446\">http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446</a> or get the svn repository url from the N2CMS page on Google Code atÂ <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/n2cms/\">http://code.google.com/p/n2cms/</a> and get the latest version.Â I prefer to get the svn version because it\'s probably more up to date.Â Next, go to the \"src\"Â folder and run the batch file to build dependencies. Now open the MVC example solution in the folder \"N2.Templates.Mvc\"\n<h3>Some Build Errors...</h3>\nI got a few build errors related to missing N2 references so I just copied these into the bin folder from the src/wwwroot folder, andÂ referencedÂ them.\n<h3>Moving to a New Project</h3>\nNow I have the MVC example running I want to copy it to a new project folder and check it into a new source control repository. Copy theN2.Templates.MvcÂ folder from the \"src\" folder, Â you can use Beyond Compare so to filter out the .svn folders.\n\nI haveÂ rearrangedÂ the Â the folder structure for svn, adding trunk/branches folders, renamed wwwroot to Project.Site and added a lib folder for the project references, and an app folder for any supporting projects.Â Next, commit everything to a new svn repository, excluding the products of builds such as the bin older and contents.\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">I\'ve also renamed the solution and project files to match the project I\'m working on, and also the assembly name and namespace for the project. Â You can use ReSharper to fix the namespaces in the source (right-click project, refactor, adjust namespaces), but you will also need to do a find and replace across the solution to make sure you change all instances of the old namespace.</span></h3>\n<span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">I also removed the namespace entries in the web.config system.web, pages, namespaces section because I like to seeÂ explicitÂ import statements, it\'s helps me understand what\'s going on. This does involve fixing the imports in pretty much every template though.</span>\n<h3>Configuring the CMS</h3>\nThe MVC templates site comes with a great selection of built in page types and parts, as well as example content. Obviously you need to sort out the example content to fit your project, but you should also disable page types and parts that are not required by the project specification. Although a client will happy take extra functionality, if you give it to them they\'ll expect it to work the way they want it to and you\'ll just create extra work for yourself. You can easily remove page types using the N2 [Disable] attribute on page class.\n<h3>Deployment Checklist</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>set checkInstallationStatus to false in web.config (&lt;installer checkInstallationStatus=\"false\" /&gt;)</li>\n	<li>enable/disable globalization in web.config</li>\n	<li>set error reporting email address in web.config</li>\n</ul>\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">References</span>\n\n<a href=\"http://interferencelogik.com/docs/N2CMS_TheLittleHandbook.pdf\">http://interferencelogik.com/docs/N2CMS_TheLittleHandbook.pdf</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446\">http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/n2cms/\">http://code.google.com/p/n2cms/</a>','Creating a new N2 CMS project','','draft','open','open','','','','','2010-05-31 21:45:14','2010-05-31 20:45:14','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=118',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (119,1,'2010-05-27 21:40:54','2010-05-27 20:40:54','First download the source code release from <a href=\"http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446\">http://n2cms.codeplex.com/releases/view/44446</a>. I\'m using the release labelled \"N2 CMS 2.0 RC2 Source Code\"\n\nMake sure you have ASP.NET MVC 2 installed.\n\nUnzip the download and run the \"Prepare Dependencies\" batch file.\n\nYou should now have an examples folder in the\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">References</span></strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://interferencelogik.com/docs/N2CMS_TheLittleHandbook.pdf\">http://interferencelogik.com/docs/N2CMS_TheLittleHandbook.pdf</a>','Creating a new N2 CMS project','','inherit','open','open','','118-revision','','','2010-05-27 21:40:54','2010-05-27 20:40:54','',118,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/05/27/118-revision/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (120,1,'2010-06-04 14:44:54','2010-06-04 13:44:54','<h3>Core Commands</h3>\n<strong>git status</strong>\n\nUse to see the status of the files an the current branch. Use <strong>git diff</strong> to get more details.\n\n<strong>git add</strong>\n\nStages files to beÂ committed. Remember that if you stage a file, then edit it, you need to stage it again for the latest edit to be committed. Use <strong>-A</strong> to stage all.\n\n<strong>git diff</strong>\n\nIf you have changed a staged file, use diff to see the details. UseÂ <strong>â€“-staged<span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"> or </span>--cached<span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"> to see the staged differences.</span></strong>\n\n<strong>git commit</strong>\n\nCommit staged changes to local repository. Use the <strong>-a</strong> options to commit unstaged changes (to tracked files)\n\n<strong>git rm</strong>\n\nRemoved a file from the staging area, and also from the working directory if it exists there. Use <strong>git rm --cached </strong>to remove a file from the staging area.\n\n<strong>gitk</strong>\n\nVisual log history.\n<h3>Undoing Things</h3>\n<strong>git reset HEAD [files]</strong>\n\nRemoves files from the staging area.\n\n<strong>git reset [hash]</strong>\n\nReset the current head to the specified state.\n\n<strong>git reset --hard</strong>\n\nMatches the working tree and index to that of the tree being switched to, losing staged changes.\n<h3>Working with Branches</h3>\n<strong>git branch</strong>\n\nLists your local branches, use <strong>git branch -r</strong> to list the remote branches.\n\n<strong>git checkout</strong>\n\nCheckout a branch to the working directory.\n<h3>Merging</h3>\n<strong>git merge [hash]</strong>\n\nMerge a commit from another branch.\n<div><strong>git checkout master</strong></div>\n<div><strong>git merge beta</strong></div>\n<div><strong>git push origin master</strong></div>\n<div>Merge beta branch into master branch</div>\n<h3>Working with Remotes</h3>\n<strong>git remote show [remote-name]</strong>\n\nGet the details of the remote repository, including branches.\n\n<strong>git remote</strong>\n\nLists your remote repositories.\n\n<strong>git fetch [remote-name]</strong>\n\nFetch changes from remote repository, but don\'t update the working directory (use <strong>rebase </strong>for that).\n\n<strong>git pull [remote-name]</strong>\n\nFetch changes from remote repository and update the working directory.\n\n<strong>git push [remote-name] [branch-name]</strong>\n\nPush your local commits to a remote repository.\n\n<strong>Tricks</strong>\n\n<strong>git update-index</strong> --assume-unchanged connectionString.config\n\nIgnore a tracked file','Git Shortcuts','','inherit','open','open','','115-autosave','','','2010-06-04 14:44:54','2010-06-04 13:44:54','',115,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/05/28/115-autosave/',0,'revision','',0);
