INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (124,1,'2010-06-02 13:56:16','2010-06-02 12:56:16','Using AJAX to send a request to an MVC action protected with a <strong>ValidateAntiForgeryToken</strong> attribute requires that you send the token along with the request data. I\'ve simply copied the value from the hidden input element (generated using <strong>Html.AntiForgeryToken</strong> in the view). Here\'s the basic JavaScript:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:javascript\">function getAntiForgeryToken()\r\n{\r\n	var tokenElement = $(\'input[name=__RequestVerificationToken]\');\r\n	var token = $(tokenElement).val();\r\n	return token;\r\n}</pre>\r\nAnd the code for making the AJAX request uses the token in its request data:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:javascript\">$.post(\'/test.html\', {__RequestVerificationToken : getAntiForgeryToken() },\r\n	function (data) {\r\n		$(\"p.message\").html(data);\r\n	}, \'json\');</pre>\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">References</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://api.jquery.com/jQuery.post/\">http://api.jquery.com/jQuery.post/</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haacked.com/archive/2009/04/02/anatomy-of-csrf-attack.aspx\">http://haacked.com/archive/2009/04/02/anatomy-of-csrf-attack.aspx</a>','ASP.NET MVC Anti Forgery Token and Ajax request','','publish','open','open','','asp-net-mvc-anti-forgery-token-and-ajax-request','','','2010-06-02 13:56:16','2010-06-02 12:56:16','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=124',0,'post','',0);
